    <h1> Scrambled Eggs with Cheese </h1>
    <h2> by Aleaya Dixon </h2>
    <p> I make this breakfast any time I have a craving something savory in the morning because it is a delicious and cheesy breakfast. Who doesn't like cheese? </p>
    <h3> Ingredients </h3>
    <ul> 
      <li> 2 large eggs </li>
      <li> 2 slices of any cheese of your choice </li>
      <li> Bacon bits (optional) </li>
    </ul>
    <h3> What to do </h3>
    <ol> 
      <li> Crack eggs into a small or medium sized bowl </li>
      <li> Rip up cheese into small pieces and put into bowl with eggs </li>
      <li> Add bacon bits if you choose </li>
      <li> Use fork or wisk everything together </li>
      <li> Spray cooking spray into a medium sized pan then poor egg mixture into pan </li>
      <li> With the pan on the stove, turn the stove on a medium-high setting </li>
      <li> Use a spatula to stir and scrape the eggs in the pan until they are cooked just how you like them </li>
      <li> Plate your eggs and enjoy! </li>
     </ol>
  </body>
